snippet.title: 2 - Texas AMBER Alert (EAS #70)
snippet.description:
UPDATES (Source is @TX_Alerts Twitter)
Updated at 2:44 PM CDT on May 14, 2020: DPS has identified a vehicle
Updated at 10:40 PM CDT on May 14, 2020: The AMBER Alert is no longer in effect. 

For More information: https://twitter.com/TX_Alerts?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Eauthor

 0:23 - I "Here" same headers 

Scroll Text: A civil authority has issued A CHILD ABDUCTION EMERGENCY for the following counties or areas: Gulf of Mexico; Orange, TX; Gulf of Mexico; Chambers, TX; Gulf of Mexico; Tyler; Jefferson; Hardin; Jasper; Newton, TX; Texas; at 8:23 PM on MAY 13, 2020 Effective until 2:23 AM. Message from KLVI AM.

https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=CAECRP&e=202005140128

BULLETIN - EAS ACTIVATION REQUESTED
CHILD ABDUCTION EMERGENCY
TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY
RELAYED BY NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE CORPUS CHRISTI TX
828 PM CDT WED MAY 13 2020

THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE TEXAS
DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY.

THIS IS A CHILD ABDUCTION ALERT ISSUED BY THE TEXAS AMBER ALERT
NETWORK

THE VAN ZANDT COUNTY SHERIFF OFFICE IS SEARCHING FOR WILLOW 
SIRMANS, WHITE, FEMALE, 14 YEARS OLD, HEIGHT 3 FEET, 75 POUNDS, 
STRAWBERRY BLONDE HAIR, BLUE EYES WITH BRACES ON HER TEETH.

POLICE ARE LOOKING FOR AUSTEN WALKER, WHITE, MALE, 21 YEARS OLD,
HEIGHT 5 FEET 9 INCHES, 140 POUNDS, BROWN HAIR, GREEN EYES, TATTOO ON
THE LEFT ARM, AND A TATTOO AND SCAR ON THE RIGHT ARM, IN CONNECTION
WITH HER ABDUCTION.

THE SUSPECT WAS LAST HEARD FROM IN GRAND SALINE, TEXAS.

LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICIALS BELIEVE THIS CHILD TO BE IN GRAVE OR
IMMEDIATE DANGER. 

IF YOU HAVE ANY INFORMATION REGARDING THIS ABDUCTION, CALL THE VAN
ZANDT COUNTY SHERIFF OFFICE.

NEWS MEDIA POINT OF CONTACT IS VAN ZANDT COUNTY SHERIFF AT 
903-567-4133.

Local Forecast (Elevator) - Kevin MacLeod
